            <section>
                <h2>Who Are We? The Modern Digital Architects</h2>
                <p>
                    Welcome to the world of a <strong>Computer Science and Engineering (CSE)</strong> student specializing in <strong>Data Science (DS)</strong>. We are the problem-solvers, the pattern-finders, and the architects of the digital future. Our journey isn't just about writing code; it's about understanding the logic behind our world and using data to make intelligent decisions.
                </p>
            </section>
            
            <section>
                <h2>&#128218; The Core Curriculum: Our Knowledge Stack</h2>
                <p>Our academic life is built on a strong foundation of core concepts. Hereâ€™s a glimpse of what fills our notebooks and IDEs:</p>
                
                <h3>Foundation CSE Subjects:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Data Structures & Algorithms (DSA):</strong> The absolute backbone of everything we do. Think of it as our grammar for programming.</li>
                    <li><strong>Object-Oriented Programming (OOP):</strong> Learning to build scalable and modular software using languages like C++ or Java.</li>
                    <li><strong>Database Management Systems (DBMS):</strong> Understanding how data is stored, retrieved, and managed efficiently.</li>
                    <li><strong>Operating Systems:</strong> Peeking under the hood of what makes a computer run.</li>
                    <li><strong>Computer Networks:</strong> Learning how data travels across the internet from one machine to another.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Data Science Specialization:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Machine Learning:</strong> Teaching computers to learn from data without being explicitly programmed. This is where the magic happens!</li>
                    <li><strong>Statistics & Probability:</strong> The mathematical foundation for making sense of data and uncertainty.</li>
                    <li><strong>Data Visualization:</strong> The art of telling a story with data using tools like Matplotlib, Seaborn, or Tableau.</li>
                    <li><strong>Big Data Technologies:</strong> Getting to grips with frameworks like Hadoop and Spark to process massive datasets.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

